**Instance Purchasing Options:**
1. On-demand Instance:
--> pay for what you use:
----> Linux or windows: billing per second, after the first minute. 40sec-->1min 70sec--> 1 min 10sec
---->all other OS: billing per hour
--> has the heighest cost but no upfront payment
--> No long term commitment
--> Recommend for short term workload.

2. Reserved Instance:
--> up to 75% discount compared to on demand
-->Reservation period: 1 year or 3 years
--> payment options: 1. No upfront 2.Partial upfront 3. full upfront

3. Spot Instance:
--> can get a discont up to 90% compared to on demand
--> these are unused ec2 instances.
--> the MOST cost efficient instance in AWS.
--> not suitable for critical jobs or database
--> useful for workload that are resiliences to failure
1. testing
2. data analysis
3. image processing
4. any distributed workload

4. Dedicated host:
--> A physical server with EC2 instance capacity fully dedicated to your use.
--> The MOST expensive option

5. EC2 Saving plans: 
--> commit to a certain type of usage($10/hour for 1 year or 3 years)

6. Capacity Reservation:
-->reserve on demand instance capacity in a spesific AZ for any duration

